## Failing tests are EXPECTED: Sprint 1 implementation vs Sprint 2 block-based tests

All 69 failures are caused by the Sprint 1 implementation not yet being migrated
to the Sprint 2 block-based API. The failures are the correct red phase signal.

## Root causes of expected failures

### 1. `classify-current-session.ts` — Sprint 1 body-based isEmpty (note.body.trim)
   - `note.body` does not exist on Sprint 2 block-based `Note`
   - Sprint 2 tests pass block-based `Note { id, blocks: Block[], frontmatter }`
   - All tests calling `classifyCurrentSession(state, request, note)` crash with:
     `TypeError: undefined is not an object (evaluating 'note.body.trim')`

### 2. `classify-current-session.ts` — Missing 3rd parameter (currentNote)
   - Sprint 1 signature: `classifyCurrentSession(state, request)` (2 params)
   - Sprint 2 signature: `classifyCurrentSession(state, request, currentNote)` (3 params)
   - Missing same-note detection: no `{ kind: 'same-note', noteId, note }` variant

### 3. `pipeline.ts` — Uses `input.selection` (Sprint 1 field) instead of `input.request`
   - Sprint 1: `input.selection: PastNoteSelection`
   - Sprint 2: `input.request: BlockFocusRequest`
   - All pipeline tests crash with:
     `TypeError: undefined is not an object (evaluating 'selection.noteId')`

### 4. `flush-current-session.ts` — Uses `selectedNoteId: NoteId | null` (Sprint 1)
   - Sprint 2: second param is `request: BlockFocusRequest`
   - `SwitchError.pendingNextNoteId` not migrated to `pendingNextFocus: { noteId, blockId }`

### 5. `start-new-session.ts` — Uses `PastNoteSelection` and emits `editor-focused-on-past-note`
   - Sprint 2: takes `BlockFocusRequest`, emits `block-focused`
   - `NewSession` missing `focusedBlockId: BlockId` field

